<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4804080>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 14–18. Larva of Rhyacophila septentrionis McLachlan 1865. 14a–14d, head: 14a, dorsal; 14b, right lateral; 14c, ventral; 14d, frontoclypeus, dorsal. 15D, 15V, mandibles from last instar larval exuviae, left (l) and right (r): 15D, dorsal; 15V, ventral. 16a, 16b, prothorax: 16a, dorsal, numbers: setae 2, 3, 5 and 6; 16b, right hemisclerite, right lateral. 17, dorsal sclerite of abdominal tergum IX. 18a–18c, details of anal prolegs: 18a, right anal claw, right lateral; 18b, detail of basolateral plate with sword process and basoventral hook, right lateral; 18c, detail of claw, right lateral. Scale bar: unlabelled = 1 mm; ● = 0.5 mm" ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4804080/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4804108>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 30–33. 30. Lectotype of Rhyacophila fasciata Hagen 1859 (male). 30a, thorax and right forewing (pinned); 30b, abdomen and male genitalia in cork-stoppered microvial (ethanol), detail. Photos: Museum of Comparative Zoology of Harvard University, Cambridge, MA, USA (MCZH). 31–33. Rhyacophila septentrionis MacLachlan 1865. 31, lectotype (male): 31a, specimen (pinned); 31b, apicodorsal lobe of segment IX and preanal appendages, dorsal view; 31c, detail of genitalia, posterior view. 32, female: 32a, cleared and mounted genitalia; 32b, original mounting preparation. 33, original mounting preparation of R. septentrionis male genitalia. Photos: Ben Price, Natural History Museum of United Kingdom (NHMUK)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4804108/files/figure.png" .

